## `test_link_to_directory_forbidden(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-hardlinks-6 -->

### Purpose
POSIX forbids hard links to directories (would introduce cycles the filesystem cannot recover from without fsck).

### Postconditions

```python
as_root.mkdir("/d")
with pytest.raises(PermissionDenied):
    as_root.link("/d", "/d-link")
```

---

## `test_unlink_decrements_nlink(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-hardlinks-7 -->

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/a"); as_root.close_fd(fd)
as_root.link("/a", "/b")
as_root.link("/a", "/c")
assert as_root.stat("/a").nlink == 3

as_root.unlink("/b")
assert as_root.stat("/a").nlink == 2
assert as_root.exists("/b") is False
assert as_root.exists("/c")
```

---

## `test_unlink_last_link_gcs_inode(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-hardlinks-8 -->

### Purpose
When `nlink` drops to 0 and no fds are open against the inode, the inode + blobs + xattrs + symlink rows are all garbage-collected in the same transaction.

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/a")
as_root.write(fd, b"payload", offset=0)
as_root.close_fd(fd)
as_root.setxattr("/a", "user.tag", b"v")

inode = as_root.stat("/a").inode

# Sanity: rows exist for this inode.
assert as_root._row_exists("nodes", inode) is True
assert as_root._count_chunks(inode) == 1
assert as_root._row_exists("xattrs_for_inode", inode) is True

# Unlink — no open fds. Inode should be GC'd.
as_root.unlink("/a")

assert as_root._row_exists("nodes", inode) is False
assert as_root._count_chunks(inode) == 0
assert as_root._row_exists("xattrs_for_inode", inode) is False
```

---

## `test_open_fd_delays_gc_past_unlink(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-hardlinks-9 -->

### Purpose
POSIX's classic "unlink-but-held-open": an inode with nlink=0 but open fds survives until the last fd closes. Reads/writes through the held fd continue to succeed.

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/a")
as_root.write(fd, b"still here", offset=0)
inode = as_root.stat("/a").inode

# Unlink while fd is still open.
as_root.unlink("/a")
assert as_root.exists("/a") is False
assert as_root._row_exists("nodes", inode) is True   # NOT yet GC'd

# Reads through the held fd still work.
assert as_root.read(fd, size=10, offset=0) == b"still here"

# Closing the fd triggers GC.
as_root.close_fd(fd)
assert as_root._row_exists("nodes", inode) is False
```

---

## `test_hard_link_xattrs_shared(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-hardlinks-10 -->

### Purpose
Xattrs are per-inode. Hard-linked paths share xattrs — setting via one path is visible via the other.

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/a"); as_root.close_fd(fd)
as_root.link("/a", "/b")

as_root.setxattr("/a", "user.tag", b"value-via-a")
assert as_root.getxattr("/b", "user.tag") == b"value-via-a"

# And vice versa.
as_root.setxattr("/b", "user.other", b"value-via-b")
assert as_root.getxattr("/a", "user.other") == b"value-via-b"
```

---

## `test_hard_link_content_shared(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-hardlinks-11 -->

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/a"); as_root.close_fd(fd)
as_root.link("/a", "/b")

# Write via /a, read via /b.
fd_a = as_root.open("/a", flags=1)   # O_WRONLY
as_root.write(fd_a, b"shared", offset=0)
as_root.close_fd(fd_a)

fd_b = as_root.open("/b", flags=0)
assert as_root.read(fd_b, size=6, offset=0) == b"shared"
as_root.close_fd(fd_b)
```

---

## `test_hard_link_independent_metadata_paths(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-hardlinks-12 -->

### Purpose
While content + xattrs + mode + inode are shared, the two *paths* have independent directory entries. `rename` on one does not affect the other.

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/a"); as_root.close_fd(fd)
as_root.link("/a", "/b")

as_root.rename("/a", "/a2")
assert as_root.exists("/a") is False
assert as_root.exists("/a2")
assert as_root.exists("/b")
assert as_root.stat("/a2").inode == as_root.stat("/b").inode
```

---

## `test_nlink_file_starts_at_one(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-hardlinks-13 -->

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/a"); as_root.close_fd(fd)
assert as_root.stat("/a").nlink == 1
```

