## `test_gc_does_not_run_while_fd_held_through_close(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-hardlinks-14 -->

### Purpose
Double check: GC runs on fd close, not on any earlier event. In particular, it does NOT run on the last `unlink` when an fd is still open.

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/a")
as_root.write(fd, b"contents", offset=0)
inode = as_root.stat("/a").inode

as_root.unlink("/a")
# Inode row still present (fd holds it).
assert as_root._row_exists("nodes", inode) is True

# Write through the held fd works.
as_root.write(fd, b"more", offset=8)
assert as_root.read(fd, size=12, offset=0) == b"contentsmore"

# Close triggers GC.
as_root.close_fd(fd)
assert as_root._row_exists("nodes", inode) is False
```

